p: \bBe careful with the books you find up here.
\bSome of them contain dangerous or confidential information!
This book seems to be filled with various cosmological horrors.
The book is titled "Dubbed Anime and Why it Isn't As Bad As You Might Think."
This floor of the library truly is filled with horrific books.
This book contains information on how to summon Darkrai.
Let's hope Persephone doesn't see this one!
\r...but the books are just so darn interesting!
This book talks about deepsea Pokemon that the government has been hiding from the population.
If the Abyssal Cult heard about this one...
This book talks about Unovan language structure.
This book talks about the creation of Delta Pokemon through experimentation- seems to be a lot more horrific than first thought.
This book seems to be purring.
On second thought, better not touch this one.
This book seems to be about the worship of Giratina.
This book seems to be about the worship of Giratina and discusses potential ways to free it.
Lots of gristly rituals are described within.
This book seems to revolve around the backstories of some prominent Ghost-type Pokemon such as Chandelure, Drifloon and Banette.
This book is written entirely in Latin- wonder why?
Hey, there's a note inside this book!
\bTo whomever should find this book and read this note...
\bThis book is the product of years of research and countless experiments conducted as a genetic engineer for the Cult of Perfection.
\bThough I admittedly was originally only interested in testing the genetic limitations of various species of Pokemon, I can no longer sit by and observe the
experiments conducted by this cult which could scarcely be referred to as humane.
\bOur leader insists that developing the perfect Pokemon is the key to our world reaching a so-called golden age.
\bBut I'm certain that his methods for acquiring his goals are incorrect.
\bThe time that I had spent playing together with Pokemon as a child have continually reminded me that the feelings and bonds that humans and Pokemon share are
\bUnfortunately it is nigh impossible to articulate this point to my colleagues, whose decisions are only swayed by data and results.
\bBut the truth is I have been carefully withholding information concerning my latest experiment, whose results will only reveal themselves after the Pokemon has
moved on past its base stage.
\bI want to create a Pokemon that will reward the trainer that raises it with love and care with a truly spectacular display, one that reminds everyone who sees it
that even as the world continues to change for the worse, there is still a hope for better change...just as the seasons change from winter to spring.
\bSadly I know that this will be my life's last work, as I know that our leader will not be pleased that I have engaged in research that he will no doubt consider to be
a waste of his precious resources.
\bHowever with the destruction of our laboratory due to that... abomination... there is no better time for me to escape with my
\bI know that the Cult of Perfection will hunt me down eventually and that I ultimately cannot see the results of my efforts come to fruition, which is where you,
whoever is reading this, come into play.
\bTake this book with you and seek out the Delta Pokemon that I allowed to escape. Use it to collect leaves from trees throughout the region as reminders of the
journey that the two of you have experienced.
\bPlease give this Pokemon the care that I was unable to provide.
\bThough I have no data to support my claims, I can assure you that you will not find your efforts wasted in the end...
Unfortunately none of the remaining books are very interesting.
Hmm...this book is completely blank except for one page which says, "Team Rocket was here."
What degenerate was responsible for this?
